  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Wash and peel the Malaysian yams, then slice them into thick fries.",
    "In a bowl, mix olive oil, garlic powder, smoked paprika, cumin powder, salt, black pepper, and herbs. Drizzle this mixture over the sliced yams and toss to coat evenly.",
    "Spread the coated yam fries onto a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Roast in the preheated oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.",
    "In another bowl, combine flour and almond flour. Mix in coconut milk until smooth.",
    "Sprinkle the crumble mixture over the roasted yams before serving as a meal complement."
